I have the same issue. It generates `Content-Type: application/javascript` in output.

The problem is that in `templatetags/js_reverse.py`, the request object is passed to views.urls_js, and in views.urls_js we have this code:
```js
    if not request:
        return response_body
    else:
        return HttpResponse(response_body, **{'content_type': 'application/javascript'})
```
So instead of returning `response_body`, it returns `HttpResponse(response_body, ...)`.

