I had trouble finding the `BoundedInt` widget in ipywidgets, seemed like it was a base class for `IntSlider`? Do you have a screen shot of the control or a link to docs I can look at for reference?

If it's similar to `IntSlider`, you'd presumably want to filter by just a single integer instead of a range, which would mean sending the same value for min/max, like this:
```
q_scale._handle_qgrid_msg_helper({
        'field': "field_name",
        'filter_info': {
            'field': "field_name",
            'max': change['new'],
            'min': change['new'],
            'type': "slider"
        },
        'type': "filter_changed"
    })
```

Also I wanted to mention that`any` is not a supported value for `type` (under `filter_info`). The possible values for that field are `slider`, `text`, `boolean`, and `date`.  Here is sample usage for the `filter_info` formats other than slider, which I already described above:

```
#Boolean:
qgrid_widget._handle_qgrid_msg_helper({
    'field': "field_name",
    'filter_info': {
        'field': "field_name",
        'selected': False,
        'type': 'boolean'
    },
    'type': "filter_changed"
})

#Text:
qgrid_widget._handle_qgrid_msg_helper({
    'field': "field_name",
    'filter_info': {
        'field': "field_name"
        'selected': [1, 3], # can also be set to 'all' in which case 'excluded' can be used
        'excluded': [] ,
        'type': 'text'
    },
    'type': "filter_changed"
})

#Date:
qgrid_widget._handle_qgrid_msg_helper({
    'field': "field_name",
    'filter_info': {
        'field': "field_name"
        'min': 1357775999999, # unit is milliseconds since the epoch
        'max': 1357171200000,
        'type': 'date'
    },
    'type': "filter_changed"
})

