> Does the method of creating the extension in ~/.jupyter/nbextensions/runselected work with a production copy for jupyter or does it require a rebuild from the git source?

It works on master, on Stable,3.x production put it into `~/.ipython/nbextensions`. For global install , `/usr/local/share/jupyter/nbextensions` should work across users. (it is a search path) 
it might need a server restart in some cases though. 


The following does configure the server to load the extension automatically, you only have to do it once. 
```
IPython.notebook.config.update({
  "load_extensions": {"runselected/main": true}
})
```

more especially it just create/update this config file:

```
~ $ cat ~/.jupyter/nbconfig/notebook.json
{
  "load_extensions": {
    "nbgrader/create_assignment": true,
    "runselected/main": true  // <- update/create this line. 
  }
}
```

So you can do it programmatically if you like. 
I did not fiddled around with my system, except symlink `~/Library/Jupyter/nbextensions` to `~/.jupyter/nbextension` so it should work for you. In particular you should see `Loaded extension: runselected/main` in Chrome console, or an error if it does not get the config.

You might need to restart the server after activating the extension though because of caching, and aggressively page refresh.

